Ladybug Tools is a collection of free computer applications that support environmental design and Of all the available environmental design software packages, Ladybug Tools is among the most comprehensive, connecting Design (CAD) interfaces to a host of validated simulation Validated Ladybug Tools is built on top of several validated simulation engines: Radiance , EnergyPlus OpenStudio , Therm Window and OpenFOAM . Free + Open Source Ladybug Tools is the only open source interface that unites all of its underlying open source Like these engines, it evolves through the consensus of an open community of Ladybug Tools is supported by a passionate and diverse community from around the Visit our online forum to see the discussions that shape our future + Downloads Ladybug Tools has been downloaded more than ,000 times and is the most popular plugin for It s also the winner of the DynaAwards for best Dynamo analysis Integrated Ladybug Tools runs within modeling software and allows data transfer between its simulation engines . So all geometry creation, simulation, and visualization happen within one Flexibile Ladybug Tools is composed of modular components , making it flexible across different stages of design and capable of answering a variety of research Parametric Ladybug Tools runs within parametric visual scripting interfaces, enabling the exploration of design spaces and the automation of Visual By harnessing capabilities of CAD interfaces, Ladybug Tools produces a variety of interactive graphics , animations, and data Ladybug Tools is written in Python , which can be run on virtually any operating system and plugged into any geometry engine (provided the geometry library is translated). Tools We are the developers of Ladybug , Honeybee , Butterfly , Dragonfly , and EPWMap We also contribute to projects including Design Explorer and the Glazing + Winter Comfort Tool . Accelerate your Community’s Transformation to Care “Where people combine their talents and efforts to design organized services for patients and local communities, extraordinary change can ” Atul Gwande Cowboys and Pit Crews Introducing the Health Commons Project Situation Today, health and social service providers in the community work on “care islands” – – while they appear close in proximity, communication and reporting barriers make it difficult for providers to track and coordinate care as an integrated Communities with fragmented systems of care produce relatively low achievement in population health and To improve population health and , communities are breaking down care silos to create connected and sustainable systems for delivery of care – – systems where providers work together to direct their specialized capabilities towards common goals for individuals and To create these fully integrated systems of care, communities are: Aligning people, processes, and incentives across organizations and sectors: medical, dental, behavioral, social service, first responders, housing, transportation, legal, education, Connecting organizations and sectors to a common technology infrastructure that enables information sharing and dissemination of best practices We are group of PNW communities, provider organizations, and technologists dedicated to creating connected and sustainable systems for delivery of We call these new systems Natural Communities of A Natural Community of Care is a fully integrated system of care where health and social service providers work together to ensure there is “No Wrong Door” for people to access the care and services they A Natural Community of Care is designed to improve the population health and of individuals and A Natural Community of Care is powered by a technology platform, called the Health Commons Network (Commons). The Commons is a communication network that digitally connects health and social service agencies in a Where agencies are connected to the Commons: Providers can share the information needed to coordinate and track care as an integrated team Organizations can disseminate strategies, workflows, and best practices that improve population health and Community Pioneers Committed to the Health Commons Project Olympic Community of Health Commons Project Clallam Commons Pilot: Addressing the Opioid Use Public Health Crisis, Primary Care Behavioral Health Integration & Care Coordination Greater Columbia ACH Commons Project Kittitas Commons Pilot: Improving Transitional Care & Care Coordination South King Health Commons Project South King Commons Pilot: Improving Diversion Care, Transitional Care & Care Coordination How to set up your Natural Community of Care When you join the Health Commons Project, you are assigned a Commons Project The team works with your organization at the “grassroots” level to create and sustain a Natural Community of The Commons Project Team follows IHI’s Pathways to Population Health Framework to ensure that your voice and goals are fully understood and there is a plan for The Commons Project Team guides you through the following steps to create a Natural Community of Care and connect to the Health Commons Network (Commons). Phase I LEARN Identify key stakeholders within your organization and across organizations sectors Work at the “grassroots” level to ensure your voice and goals are fully understood Understand the current gaps in care affecting community members and patients Define a shared vision of your community goals, success measures, and team commitments Prioritize which community services you would like to connect to the Health Commons Network Phase II ACT Design workflows to support connectivity between agencies Match needs wants of agencies to innovations Complete pilot test of new workflows technologies, prove utility, and connect to the Heath Commons Network Roll out the Health Commons Network to Natural Community of Care stakeholders until services are fully integrated Phase III IMPROVE Establish benchmark and target measures Complete “Plan-Do-Study-Act” (PDSA) cycles until target measures are reached Measure and sustain Health Commons Network in partnership with regional Accountable Communities of Health and Managed Care Organizations Connecting Natural Communities of Care to the Health Commons Network The Health Commons Network (Commons) is a digital communication system that connects health and social service agencies in a Where agencies in a Natural Community of Care are connected to the Commons: Providers can share the information needed to coordinate and track care as an integrated team Organizations can disseminate strategies, workflows, and best practices that improve population health and Before the Commons Network After the Commons Network The Commons supports a wide ra

Before It Gets Any " Don’t sacrifice the lifestyle you desire over problems that can be That’s why we made this just for Get Your Free Tips Report Here Get Your Free Tips Report Here Ben Bagge PT, DPT, CSCS Founder of Pro+Kinetix Physical Therapy & Performance A Message From Ben Bagge, Owner & Founder of Pro+Kinetix Physical Therapy & Performance When it comes to living with neck and shoulder pain, everybody we see wants to know: “Why is this happening to me?” “Why am I still suffering with neck and shoulder pain after putting up with it for 6 months - sometimes more?” Most people think that when they get Neck or Shoulder Pain, the pain is going to go away on its That they’ll wake up one morning and like “magic”, it’ll be as if it never happened… But then 6 months later you’re still living with nagging pain even worse than it was when it came Does That Sound Like You? Another scenario we see all the time in our physical therapy clinic is when people go to the Doctors, and the Doctor tells them to rest and “try these painkillers” to “see how it goes”. But then 6 weeks later, they end up going back to the same Doctor again because it hasn’t gotten any better, only to be given ANOTHER prescription of even stronger Has That Ever Happened To You? Maybe you are confused because you’ve been told different things by different Maybe you think you have a neck problem – but it’s actually your shoulder where the problem It’s a very confusing part of the body to work out where the problem is, and this often leads people to procrastinate and put off making a decision about what to do to help fix their neck and shoulder Worse, many people just end up accepting it as ‘part of life’ – as if it’s normal or “has” to be that Is This How You Feel? If You’re Currently Living With Neck And Or Shoulder Pain, Here’s 7 More Reasons Why It Could Be Lasting Longer Than It Should: You thought it would go away on it’s own – but it didn’t You went to the Doctor who told you to rest and take painkillers – but the pills did nothing to help, and as soon as they wore off neck and shoulder pain struck again A family member, or friend, told you that everybody gets neck and shoulder pain as they get older, so you just accepted it You sought help from other Healthcare Professionals or a Physical Therapist in the past, but nothing they said or did seemed to help You’ve tried using things like heating pads or TENS but they’ve done nothing to help make the pain better You thought it would be a good idea to rest because your neck or shoulder pain was so bad, but it still irritates you daily You decided to get a few “massages” hoping that would fix the pain, but all they did was feel nice and relaxing, and didn’t do anything to fix it long term If any of these have happened to you – we would love to help you by inviting you to book a call to talk with one of our Physical Therapists to find out what can be done to help The fact that you’ve tried any or all of these things, means that we know what doesn’t work – which means we are closer to finding what Click the link below

Liquidity, faster &, cheaper transactions, digitally recorded information rather than offline records and access to the free market of billions of individuals around the world who can now invest in your offering and play a bigger role in your The digital token structure give us the ability to program SmartCompliance into each token to enable trading within legal & regulatory parameters and to program in tracking of the tokens for automated, smart contract managed reporting and distribution How is real estate ownership tied to tokens? Each security token represents a static, fractional percentage of total ownership in the underlying real estate asset, project or Every token offering is fractionalized by the same logic to ensure pricing transparency and Who can particpate in my security token offering? Chiefs -- -- -- -- COMPENSATORY PICKS Pick Team Round 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 Determining Draft Order Determination of Draft order for the NFL teams is based on the record and playoff finish by each team in that For the teams that did not make the playoffs, order is determined by overall season record with the worst record picking For the teams that made the playoffs, the rest of the picks are ordered by playoff record with the teams that lose getting lower picks based on which round they were ousted and the Super Bowl winner getting the last For the playoff teams that got eliminated in the same round, their order is determined by regular season Overall ties are then broken by strength of schedule, which is a calculation of the combined record of all of a team’s opponents in that year, with divisional opponents counting The next tie breaker is record against conference opponents and then divisional The final tie breaker is a coin flip, if tie still After the first round, the order is determined by revolving the teams with the same records with the team that just picked first of the group picking last in the next If there is an expansion team, that team will pick first, and if there are two expansion teams, they will flip a coin with one team getting the first pick in the draft and the other in the expansion draft of current image svg+xml image svg+xml Columns Studs & Duds Thanks to the traditional bedding industry, people have come to identify themselves with a single sleeping position when choosing a pillow, but research shows we actually toss and turn throughout the Note: This doesn’t mean a single pillow would work for Instead, let s use your data to build your pillow and break free from current confusing pillow Start Simple We think pillows should be breathable, , and bounce In a world filled with great technologies, we also believe electronics shouldn’t have a place near our heads when we We just want a great pillow that uses innovative materials and better yet, they should be personalized to us for optimized support and comfort — all at a great price How We Got Here So we set out to create Our pillows were developed from hundreds of stories about the way you sleep, and we on why you liked and didn’t like the pillows you’ve Then, we tried them all — shredded foam pillows, bamboo pillows, latex pillows, down pillows, traditional memory foam pillows, and adjustable After prototyping and testing alongside partners with years of material research while tapping into the training and education of sleep researchers, we learned what goes into making a thoughtful pillow — not a “smart” The Missing Piece Is You The right foams seem to provide great support, but we can’t shake the love and familiarity of a plush, fluffy, That’s why our pillows are a hybrid design constructed with a foam inner core and an outer plush pillow, both unique to your individual Foam provides our pillows with a supportive core, and we’ll match you with the right one (learn more about our foams here ). This is encased within an outer pillow that adds a soft fluff — featuring fibers that allow us to play with thickness, length, and quantity for the type of cushioning effect you The last piece of the puzzle is you: we personalize the best materials to your questionnaire Our product designs aren t set in We re always listening to what you have to say and tweaking our products to improve your Get in touch! Remember to set your timeout to seconds to ensure this process goes In cases where every request fails in seconds we will return a error, you may retry the request and you will not be charged for the unsuccessful request (you are only charged for successful requests, and status codes). Make sure to catch these errors! They will occur on roughly % of requests for hard to scrape If you exceed your plan concurrent connection limit, the API will respond with a status code, this can be solved by slowing down your request rate There is no overage allowed on the free plan, if you exceed requests per month on the free plan, you will receive a Each request will return a string containing the raw html from the page requested, along with any headers and Basic Usage Scraper API exposes a single API endpoint, simply send a GET request to http: api.scraperapi.com with two query string parameters, api_key which contains your API key, and url which contains the url you would like to Sample Code Bash Node Python Scrapy PHP Ruby curl "http: api.scraperapi.com?api_key=YOURAPIKEY&url=http: httpbin.org ip" var request = require( request ) var url = http: httpbin.org ip request( method: GET , url: http: api.scraperapi.com ?api_key=YOURAPIKEY&url= + url, headers: Accept: application json , , , function(error, response, body) (body) ) import requests payload = api_key : YOURAPIKEY, url : https: httpbin.org ip r = ( http: api.scraperapi.com , params=payload) print # ...your parsing logic here yield ( http: api.scraperapi.com ?api_key=YOURAPIKEY&url= + url, ) <?php $ch = curl_init() $url = "http: httpbin.org ip" curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_URL, "http: api.scraperapi.com ?api_key=YOURAPIKEY&url=".$url) curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_RETURNTRANSFER, TRUE) curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_HEADER, FALSE) curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_HTTPHEADER, array( "Accept: application json" )) $response = curl_exec($ch) curl_close($ch) var_dump($response) require httparty url = http: api.scraperapi.com query = api_key = YOURAPIKEY , url = http: httpbin.org ip response = ( http: api.scraperapi.com , query: query) results = puts results Result <html <head < head <body <pre style="word-wrap: : " "origin":"176.12.80.34" < pre < body < html Rendering Javascript If you are crawling a page that requires you to render the javascript on the page, we can fetch these pages using a headless This feature is only available on the Business and Enterprise To render javascript, simply set render=true and we will use a headless Google Chrome instance to fetch the page: Sample Code Bash Node Python Scrapy PHP Ruby curl "http: api.scraperapi.com?api_key=YOURAPIKEY&url=http: httpbin.org ip&render=true" var request = require( request ) var url = http: httpbin.org ip request( method: GET , url: http: api.scraperapi.com ?api_key=YOURAPIKEY&url= + url + &render=true , headers: Accept: application json , , , function(error, response, body) (body) ) import requests payload = api_key : YOURAPIKEY, url : https: httpbin.org ip , render : true r = ( http: api.scraperapi.com , params=payload) print # And when you experience those low testosterone symptoms, how do you know it’s because of “low T” and not some other medical condition? All adult men begin to lose their testosterone as they Thing is, some experience a much steeper drop, accompanied by more severe Yes, low levels of the male sex hormone will translate into a lower sex drive—but that’s only part of Low Testosterone In this guide, we uncover the facts about low “T” that every guy should know: Most common symptoms of low testosterone Reasons why men lose their “T” Proven ways to increase your male sex hormone naturally The truth about testosterone boosters and supplements When to speak to a doctor Before we dig into low testosterone symptoms in men, it’s a good idea to have an understanding of what testosterone is and how it affects adult Let’s start with the basics … Table of Contents Why does low testosterone matter? When to speak to your doctor Why does low testosterone matter? Testosterone is the main sex hormone in It is primarily produced by the testicles, though small amounts are also made by the adrenal Testosterone is an androgen hormone, which means it plays a critical role in the development of male characteristics and reproductive Testosterone plays several important roles in men, including: Development of the penis and testes Libido (sex drive) Muscle strength and growth Bone density Production of red blood cells Sperm production Mood and behavior Cognitive function Male development at puberty: deepening of the voice, growth of facial hair and pubic hair, muscle growth and reproduction functions Testosterone levels fluctuate in men throughout the day , peaking in the morning and hitting a low point in the The brain controls the production of testosterone, sending signals to the pituitary gland, which in turn sends signals to the That is where the production Your body uses a “feedback loop” to regulate testosterone levels in the Scientists at Harvard Health explain : “When testosterone levels rise too high, the brain sends signals to the pituitary to reduce ” The opposite is also true: when levels are too low, the brain says, “Hey, let’s ramp up production down ” But if your body is unable to, for whatever reason, that’s when the low testosterone symptoms set In men, this inability to produce normal levels of testosterone is a medical condition known as Here’s what it can look like … Common Symptoms Of Low Testosterone In Men Symptoms of low testosterone can manifest themselves in several different Below, we take a deep dive into the most common low testosterone signs and how they’re experienced by the average But again, it’s important to remember that these symptoms are very similar to those of other, potentially serious medical symptoms are typically most noticeable in men whose testosterone falls below “normal” But a slight drop (or slight incline , for that matter) generally won’t make a noticeable difference, unless you’re falling in or out of the normal range for your Wondering how to tell if you have low testosterone? Here are some of the most common symptoms and signs of low testosterone in men: Reduced interest in sex Not surprisingly, when your main sex hormone is in short supply, it negatively affects your desire for A loss of libido is the most common and most noticeable symptom of low In an interview with CBS News, Abraham Morgentaler, associate clinical professor of medicine at Harvard Medical School and the author of “Testosterone for Life,” explained how men with low “T” typically lose their sexual desire: “Testosterone is what’s responsible for ‘the grrr factor’ [in men],” he Every guy is different when it comes to how often they want But when their testosterone is low, a man’s appetite for sex is virtually “absent.” However, other Harvard researchers warn that it’s still too early to determine how low testosterone levels affect sex While we know that testosterone is key for libido and healthy sexual function, more research needs to be done on the hormone’s relationship to

This represents a new, paradigm, and it s what we work on daily at Controlling Carbon Emissions So much of our global chemical production is reliant on oil and natural gas, which inevitably produces carbon dioxide waste . Despite global efforts to prevent excessive carbon dioxide emissions and limit climate change, we need more aggressive solutions that change industrial processes for a greener future . To solve this core emissions issue, we are creating a device for generating products from carbon monoxide (CO) with cheap electricity , which integrates with current natural gas infrastructure and upcoming carbon dioxide (CO 2 ) transformation The CO we need can be directly and effectively produced from CO 2 waste through green production equipment - after that, we make the more complex, chemicals our society needs What sets us apart from competing direct CO 2 conversion is our ability to with other feedstocks to make specialty This capability opens new market opportunities with every chemical product, and our scalable technology can match any volume required with Our library is constantly expanding! Whether you’re a CISO or a wannabe CISO, the series delivers inside tips on how to manage a security team, and how to focus your precious resources to create a secure environment for your employees and We also get the insight from security vendors as to best practices and what it takes to truly form customer David Spark David Spark David Spark ( ) is the creator, author, and producer of the CISO Security Vendor Relationship He’s a veteran tech journalist and founder of Spark Media Solutions , a B2B content marketing agency for the tech and security Spark has been the creative director, producer, voice, and face of many content marketing campaigns for numerous Fortune B2B tech and security companies . For more than years, Spark and his articles have appeared in more than media outlets including eWEEK, Wired News, Forbes, PCWorld, ABC Radio, John Dvorak’s “Cranky Geeks,” KQED’s “This Week in Northern California,” and TechTV (formerly ZDTV). Spark has also worked for many advertising agencies, most recently Publicis Dialog where he launched the agency’s new media Outside of tech, security, and marketing, Spark squandered more than a dozen years working as a touring stand up comedian , a San Francisco tour guide, and comedy writer for The Second City in Speaking Given his background, Spark speaks, entertains, and moderates at tech and marketing He also offers a variety of engaging training programs and talks, such as: What CISOs Want : The CISO Security Vendor Relationship Series boiled down to just the best parts in a or less Perfect for sales teams eager to try to understand the CISO More Schmooze, Less Snooze: How to Deliver “The Most Talked About” Conference Session : Interview and crowd control techniques primarily for moderators, but also panelists and even audience members on how to run a session that attendees rave Business Networking Pickup Lines : Entertaining games and exercises that teach the art of business Three Feet from Seven Figures: Engagement Techniques to Qualify More Leads at Trade Shows : When manning a trade show booth, how do you stop, engage, and qualify potential leads? OP AL | Case Study Work Studio OP AL parametric icons lottie OP AL is a resource that helps users easily customize and download a set of animated icons as code, ready to be Visit to see it Your browser doesn t support HTML5 Download the video :00 0 0 0 :00 This project emerged from a fascination with json files and the possibilities of live animation, driven by By tinkering with json files, we found relationships that established how certain variables affected the One of the most important discoveries was that OP (outPoint) AL (animationLength) = FR (frameRate) . This equation allowed us to dictate the duration of animations after they had been exported, and from that, OP AL was We created the animated icon set OP AL to provide the design community with a resource that has the flexibility to fit thousands of different use using Lottie and json files, we were able to create something powerful enough to accomplish all of this, but light enough to make an entire animated set around the size of a The goal of our approach was to provide as much creative autonomy as we could to the user, while still ensuring the generated icons communicated The most important constraints for guaranteeing readability were the use of stroke and counterstrokes, and adhering the icons to a pixel Because the design of each icon was determined from its smallest and thickest possible iterations, they’ll always remain legible despite changes in scale or stroke While the design constraints helped in creating the set initially, animation is where we were most excited to explore the code and create This allowed us to set limits and relationships for certain variables, providing an additional level of quality control to the assets the tool Though this project was originally conceived as a vehicle for exploration in json, it evolved into a more specific and directed Its final form allowed us to contribute to a larger goal of visioning design and
